<article id="post-876" class="post-876 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-careers category-general category-technology tag-critical-mass tag-experience-matters tag-google tag-rich-media tag-rolex">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/google-maps-in-a-flash/" rel="bookmark">Google Maps in (a) Flash!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Yesterday, we posted a new part to <a href="http://www.rolex.com/">Rolex.com</a>: the ability to <a href="http://www.rolex.com/en/inside-rolex/sales-service/find-a-rolex-dealer/index.jsp">find a local Authorised Rolex Dealer</a>. This on its own is hardly breaking any new ground &#8212; it&#8217;s a fairly routine piece of functionality. To help you find your local dealer, we provided a map &#8212; a <a href="http://maps.google.com/">Google Map</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><img src="http://experiencematters.criticalmass.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/google-maps-flash-rolexcom.jpg" alt="Google Maps Flash Interface" /></p>
<p>Those of you who know the two technologies are probably now scratching your heads. Google Maps. Flash. Aren&#8217;t they incompatible?<br />
Not any more.<br />
<a href="http://experiencematters.criticalmass.com/2007/12/14/google-maps-in-a-flash/#more-142" class="more-link">Continue reading &#8220;Google Maps in (a) Flash!&#8217;</a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/google-maps-in-a-flash/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2007-12-14T15:14:17-07:00">14 December 2007</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/careers/" rel="category tag">Careers</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/critical-mass/" rel="tag">critical mass</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/experience-matters/" rel="tag">experience matters</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/google/" rel="tag">google</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/rich-media/" rel="tag">rich media</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/rolex/" rel="tag">rolex</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/google-maps-in-a-flash/#comments">4 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Google Maps in (a) Flash!</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
